<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rue2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rue,</orth> vb. 1) to grieve for, to regret, to lament: absol.: <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.325" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 325</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.117" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 2, 14</bibl>. Transitively: <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.323" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 323</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.205" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 205</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.109" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.43" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.222" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 222</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.6.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 6, 42</bibl>.<lb />2) to pity: <cit><quote>r. the tears I shed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 105</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Ruth.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>